<!-- Point of view — sticky heading + numbered tenets + decorative ledger -->
<section class="section section-pov">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="pov-grid">

      <!-- Sticky title column -->
      <aside class="pov-aside">
        <div class="pov-aside-inner reveal">
          <p class="eyebrow">Our point of view</p>
          <h2>Design that<br><em>earns its keep.</em></h2>
          <p class="pov-aside-meta">Three principles we won&rsquo;t bend on.</p>
        </div>
      </aside>

      <!-- Numbered tenets list — large, editorial -->
      <ol class="pov-tenets" role="list">
        <li class="pov-tenet reveal">
          <span class="pov-tenet-num" aria-hidden="true">01</span>
          <h3 class="pov-tenet-headline">The brief is the bug.</h3>
          <p>Most design work fails because the brief is wrong. Teams ask for a redesign when they need positioning. They ask for a logo when they need a customer. We start by asking which decision the design has to make easier — then work backwards from there.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="pov-tenet reveal">
          <span class="pov-tenet-num" aria-hidden="true">02</span>
          <h3 class="pov-tenet-headline">Useful beats perfect.</h3>
          <p>We&rsquo;re partial to short engagements with clear deliverables. We&rsquo;d rather ship something useful in two weeks than something polished in two quarters. If you need a 90-page brand bible, we are not the right studio.</p>
        </li>
        <li class="pov-tenet reveal">
          <span class="pov-tenet-num" aria-hidden="true">03</span>
          <h3 class="pov-tenet-headline">Metric or it didn&rsquo;t happen.</h3>
          <p>Every project we take on has a stated metric and a stated deadline. If we can&rsquo;t write both in one sentence, we&rsquo;re not ready to start.</p>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </div>

    <!-- Ledger strip: animated proof bars at the bottom of the section -->
    <div class="pov-ledger reveal">
      <div class="pov-ledger-item">
        <span class="pov-ledger-label">In business</span>
        <span class="pov-ledger-value" data-count="6" data-suffix=" yrs">0</span>
        <span class="pov-ledger-bar"><span class="pov-ledger-bar-fill" style="--w: 60%"></span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="pov-ledger-item">
        <span class="pov-ledger-label">Clients who renew or refer</span>
        <span class="pov-ledger-value" data-count="93" data-suffix="%">0</span>
        <span class="pov-ledger-bar"><span class="pov-ledger-bar-fill" style="--w: 93%"></span></span>
      </div>
      <div class="pov-ledger-item">
        <span class="pov-ledger-label">Spent on outbound sales, ever</span>
        <span class="pov-ledger-value pov-ledger-value-zero">$0</span>
        <span class="pov-ledger-bar"><span class="pov-ledger-bar-fill" style="--w: 0%"></span></span>
      </div>
    </div>

  </div>
</section>

<!-- Values — bordered grid, no boxed cards -->
<section class="section section-values-bg">
  <div class="container">
    <header class="section-head section-head-left">
      <p class="eyebrow">How we operate</p>
      <h2>Four rules<br>we won&rsquo;t bend.</h2>
    </header>
    <ul class="value-grid" role="list">
      <li class="value-item reveal" role="listitem">
        <p class="value-num">01</p>
        <h3>Ship the obvious thing first</h3>
        <p>The boring 80% always beats the clever 100%. We design what users actually need before we design what looks good in a portfolio.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="value-item reveal" role="listitem">
        <p class="value-num">02</p>
        <h3>Strategy is a deliverable</h3>
        <p>Every engagement starts with a one-page strategy brief. If we can&rsquo;t write the why in one page, we&rsquo;re not ready to design.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="value-item reveal" role="listitem">
        <p class="value-num">03</p>
        <h3>Async by default</h3>
        <p>We protect maker time. Communication happens in Notion and Slack threads, not calls. Calls are reserved for decisions only.</p>
      </li>
      <li class="value-item reveal" role="listitem">
        <p class="value-num">04</p>
        <h3>One throat to choke</h3>
        <p>You get one senior designer from kickoff to launch. No account managers, no handoffs, no junior shadow team working off-screen.</p>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</section>

